Kenya yesterday donated $5 million (Sh500 million) to the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria.This is one of the largest contributions from Africa. The announcement was made by Foreign Affairs CS Amina Mohamed who spoke on behalf of President Uhuru Kenyatta at the Global Fund Replenishment conference in Montreal, Canada. The Global Fund has played a major role in supporting Kenya s success in combating HIV-Aids, Tuberculosis and Malaria over the years, she said. The donation is part of the concept of giving to receive. Countries that get cash from the global fund also make contributions. Kenya is expected to receive more than Sh34 billion from the fund in three years.